# Field Visibility & Role-Based Access

This codebase decides who sees what data through the AND of three
independent axes: **role** (user_type), **scope** (org/policy/agent),
and **field config** (meta). The full contract is spread across four
files and is NOT obvious from reading any single one. Get it wrong
and either an end-user sees something they must not (Net Premium
leaking to a client) or an admin loses a column they need (a Premium
tab going blank).

If your task touches **any** of the following, STOP and read
[`.cursor/skills/field-visibility-roles/SKILL.md`](mdc:.cursor/skills/field-visibility-roles/SKILL.md)
**before** writing code:

- Adding or renaming a value in `userTypeEnum` (`db/schema/core.ts`)
- Editing `lib/auth/rbac.ts` (`canCreatePolicy`, `policyScopeWhere`,
  `userHasOrgAccess`, `assertOrgAccess`)
- Editing `lib/policy-access.ts` `canAccessPolicy`
- Editing `lib/auth/active-org.ts` (`resolveActiveOrgId`,
  `isAdminLike`)
- Editing `lib/accounting-fields.ts` `filterFieldsByContext`,
  `AccountingFieldDef`, or `loadAccountingFields`
- Editing `app/api/policies/[id]/premiums/route.ts` `userTypeToContext`
  / `applyDefaultRoleFilter` / the two-pass filter call site
- Editing `PREMIUM_CONTEXT_OPTIONS` in `EditPackageFieldClient.tsx`
  / `NewPackageFieldClient.tsx` / `GenericFieldsManager.tsx`
- Adding a new "Show in X tabs" or "Visible to" config to any
  `form_options.meta` shape
- Adding a new role-gated UI surface (sidebar entry, dashboard tile,
  per-action button)
- Diagnosing "user X sees a field they shouldn't" / "user Y can't
  see a field they should" / "client logged in and saw Net Premium" /
  "Premium tab is blank for admin after configuring contexts"

## The 30-second cheatsheet

| Concern | Pattern | Don't do |
|---|---|---|
| Org-scope on a list endpoint | `policyScopeWhere(user)` from `lib/auth/rbac.ts` | Inline membership join |
| Per-policy access in any policy endpoint | `canAccessPolicy(user, policyId)` from `lib/policy-access.ts` | Re-derive agent / membership rules per route |
| Resolve which org a request acts on | `resolveActiveOrgId` from `lib/auth/active-org.ts` | Trust `body.organisationId` blindly |
| Map `user_type` to "admin-like" | `isAdminLike(user)` from `lib/auth/active-org.ts` | Check `user.userType === "admin"` only — forgets `internal_staff` |
| Premium tab visibility | `filterFieldsByContext` + second-pass `userTypeToContext` (see route lines 551–560) | Hard-code role checks in the component |
| Net Premium hidden from clients | Today: keep `applyDefaultRoleFilter` running (don't set `premiumContexts`), OR uncheck `Client` on Net Premium. **Proper fix is config-driven, NOT hardcoded** — see skill §6.1 + the [`dynamic-config-first` skill](mdc:.cursor/skills/dynamic-config-first/SKILL.md) §3.2 (`form_options.user_type_visibility`). | Hardcode `if (userType === "client" && role === "net") hide()` — that's the same anti-pattern the dynamic-config-first skill forbids |
| Documents (audience rules) | Defer to the `document-user-rights` skill | Reinvent audience rules inline |
| `direct_client` policy list / linked endorsements | Defer to the `client-policy-scope` skill | Reuse plain `/api/policies` for `?linkedPolicyId=` |
| New `user_type` value | Update `userTypeEnum` + `userTypeToContext` + `applyDefaultRoleFilter` + `audiencesForRole` + the matrix in the skill | Add the enum value and assume defaults work |

## Known gaps (read the skill before "fixing")

These are documented in the skill and are NOT silent bugs:

- **Net Premium leaks to clients** when any field has
  `premiumContexts` set (the legacy fallback stops running). Skill §6.1.
- **"Our commission" / broker margin** is not modeled — the formula
  engine has no `IF` and there's no `brokerCommissionCents` column.
  Skill §6.2.
- **Endorsement agentId** falls back to parent — never drop that
  fallback in `canAccessPolicy`. Skill §6.4.

If anything above is unclear, the skill has the full contract, the
matrix, and an executable verification recipe (SQL + manual UI smoke
test) you can run to confirm correctness.
